{"title_page": "Rahul Kohli", "text_new": "{{short description|British actor}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=November 2016}}\n{{primary sources|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use British English | date = April 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Rahul Kohli\n| image            = Rahul Kohli April 2015.jpg\n| caption          = Kohli at Wondercon, April 2015\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1985|11|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[London]], England, United Kingdom\n| occupation       = Actor\n| known_for        = ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]''\n| notable_works    = \n| television       = \n| spouse           = \n| children         = \n| alma_mater       = \n| website          = \n| years_active     = 2007\u2013present\n}}\n'''Rahul Kohli''' (born 13 November 1985) is a British actor. He is best known for playing Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti in the television series, ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]'', and for his guest appearances on the YouTube channel, [[Rooster Teeth#Funhaus|Funhaus]].\n\n==Early life==\nRahul Kohli was born in [[London, England]], to [[Hindu]] immigrant parents of Indian heritage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/67677/20150705/rahul-kohli-5-things-you-must-know-about-the-izombie-star.htm |title=Rahul Kohli: 5 Things You Must Know About The 'iZombie' Star |last=Cornejo |first=Jordianne |website=Fashion & Style |date=5 July 2015 |accessdate=24 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706124920/http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/67677/20150705/rahul-kohli-5-things-you-must-know-about-the-izombie-star.htm |archive-date=6 July 2015}}</ref> His mother was born and raised in [[Thailand]] and his father is from [[Kenya]].{{third-party inline|date=November 2016}} He began acting as a young boy in school plays. At age 17, he decided to pursue acting as a career, going on to study media studies at [[Uxbridge College]], and later attending drama school, where he trained in stage performing.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nKohli was part of several stage productions during his time in drama school, and acted at the [[Royal National Theatre]], in productions like ''[[Henry V (play)|Henry V]]'' and ''Sabato, domenica e luned\u00ec''.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nKohli is [[colourblind]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Career==\nAfter completing school, Kohli found an agent and began working in television, making appearances in established series ''[[Holby City]]'' (2012) and ''[[EastEnders]]'' (2013), as well as advertisements for major brands, such as [[Sony]] and [[Heineken]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} Although no longer his focus, he continued to work on the stage as well, including a period of time at the [[Royal National Theatre]] working with acclaimed director [[Howard Davies (director)|Howard Davies]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nShortly after moving to [[Los Angeles]],{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} Kohli was cast in a lead role in the television series, ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]'' (2015\u201319), as Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti.<ref name = Rolling>{{cite web|author=Rachel Weber |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/actor-rahul-kohli-on-converting-izombie-costars-to-gaming-2-191669/ |title=Actor Rahul Kohli on Converting \u2018iZombie\u2019 Costars to Gaming |publisher=Rolling Stone|date=9 March 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> He appeared in all 71 episodes of the show. Other notable credits include the 2018 film, ''[[Happy Anniversary (2018 film)|Happy Anniversary]]'';<ref>{{cite web|author=Amanda N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/rahul-kohli-happy-anniversary-netflix-denis-menochet-lior-ashkenazi-entebbe-movie-1201903469/ |title=Rahul Kohli Joins Netflix Comedy \u2018Happy Anniversary\u2019; Denis M\u00e9nochet & Lior Ashkenazi Cast In \u2018Entebbe\u2019 |publisher=Deadline |date=7 February 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'' (2017\u201319);<ref>{{cite web|author=Christina Radish |url=https://collider.com/rahul-kohli-supergirl-season-2-interview/ |title=\u2018Supergirl\u2019: Rahul Kohli on His Character\u2019s Arrival in National City on Tonight\u2019s Episode|publisher=Collider |date=24 April 2017 |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Sam Stone |url=https://www.cbr.com/supergirl-rahul-kohli-season-5/ |title=Supergirl Welcomes Back iZombie's Rahul Kohli for Season 5 |publisher=CBR.com|date=28 August 2019|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> and the animated TV series, ''[[Harley Quinn (TV series)|Harley Quinn]]'' (2019\u20132020). Kohli will also be appearing in the upcoming series, ''[[The Haunting of Bly Manor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Anthony D'Alessandro |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/netflix-haunting-of-bly-manor-cast-izombie-rahul-kohli-catherine-parker-1202708101/ |title=\u2018iZombie\u2019s Rahul Kohli Joins \u2018Haunting Of Bly Manor\u2019 Posse; Catherine Parker Returning To Netflix Anthology Series |publisher=Deadline |date=30 August 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKohli is a fan of [[Liverpool football club|Liverpool Football Club]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}} He is very active on [[Twitter]] and an avid gamer.<ref name = Rolling>{{cite web|author=Rachel Weber |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/actor-rahul-kohli-on-converting-izombie-costars-to-gaming-2-191669/ |title=Actor Rahul Kohli on Converting \u2018iZombie\u2019 Costars to Gaming |publisher=Rolling Stone|date=9 March 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> Since 2015, he has featured in several [[Rooster Teeth]] videos for [[Rooster Teeth#Funhaus|Funhaus]], [[Kinda Funny]], and [[Achievement Hunter]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Partial filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''The Vacancy''\n| Tom\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Alone Together''\n| Ahmed\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''I'll Be Home Soon''\n| Waseem\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Gangsters Gamblers Geezers''\n| Dev\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Happy Anniversary (2018 film)|Happy Anniversary]]''\n| Ed\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''My Holiday Hostage Hell''\n| Navi\n| Episode: \"West Papau\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Holby City]]''\n| Cal Nelson\n| Episode: \"Blood Money\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[EastEnders]]''\n| Manager\n| Episode: 16 April 2013\n|-\n| 2015\u20132019\n| ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]''\n| Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2017\u201319\n| ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]''\n| Jack Spheer\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\u20132020\n| ''[[Harley Quinn (TV series)|Harley Quinn]]''\n| [[Scarecrow (DC Comics)|Dr. Jonathan Crane / Scarecrow]]<br>(voice)\n| Recurring role\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The Rocketeer (2019 TV series)|The Rocketeer]]''\n| Aarush Cheena (voice)\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The Haunting of Bly Manor]]''\n|\n|\n|}\n\n===Web series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Red vs. Blue]]''\n| Male Tex\n| Episode: \"Get Bent\"\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Sex Swing''\n| Rahul\n| Episode: \"Welcome to the Clam Jam\"\n|-\n|2017\u2013present\n|''[[Funhaus]]''\n| Himself\n| Series: \"''My Boyfriend'' Gameplay\" <br/> Series: \"''Talking Stalkings'' Episode 3\"\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Rage 2]]''\n|Garcia the Gregarious\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Gears 5]]''\n| Fahz Chutani\n| \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=3418510}}\n* {{Twitter|id=RahulKohli13}}\n* [http://www.tvguide.com/news/izombie-rahul-kohli-ravi-chakrabarti/ \"iZombie's Rahul Kohli Explains Why We Won't Learn More About Ravi Anytime Soon\"] on ''[[TV Guide]]''\n* [http://www.glixel.com/interviews/rahul-kohli-is-converting-his-izombie-costars-to-gaming-w470713 \"Actor Rahul Kohli on Converting His 'iZombie' Costars to Gaming\"] on ''[[Glixel]]''\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kohli, Rahul}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English people of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Kenyan descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Thai descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People with color blindness]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British actor}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=November 2016}}\n{{primary sources|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use British English | date = April 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Rahul Kohli\n| image            = Rahul Kohli April 2015.jpg\n| caption          = Kohli at Wondercon, April 2015\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1985|11|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[London]], England, United Kingdom\n| occupation       = Actor\n| known_for        = ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]''\n| notable_works    = \n| television       = \n| spouse           = \n| children         = \n| alma_mater       = \n| website          = \n| years_active     = 2007\u2013present\n}}\n'''Rahul Kohli''' (born 13 November 1985) is a British actor. He is best known for playing Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti in the television series, ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]'', and for his guest appearances on the YouTube channel, [[Rooster Teeth#Funhaus|Funhaus]].\n\n==Early life==\nRahul Kohli was born in [[London, England]], to [[Hindu]] immigrant parents of Indian heritage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/67677/20150705/rahul-kohli-5-things-you-must-know-about-the-izombie-star.htm |title=Rahul Kohli: 5 Things You Must Know About The 'iZombie' Star |last=Cornejo |first=Jordianne |website=Fashion & Style |date=5 July 2015 |accessdate=24 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706124920/http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/67677/20150705/rahul-kohli-5-things-you-must-know-about-the-izombie-star.htm |archive-date=6 July 2015}}</ref> His mother was born and raised in [[Thailand]] and his father is from [[Kenya]].{{third-party inline|date=November 2016}} He began acting as a young boy in school plays. At age 17, he decided to pursue acting as a career, going on to study media studies at [[Uxbridge College]], and later attending drama school, where he trained in stage performing.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nKohli was part of several stage productions during his time in drama school, and acted at the [[Royal National Theatre]], in productions like ''[[Henry V (play)|Henry V]]'' and ''Sabato, domenica e luned\u00ec''.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nKohli is [[colourblind]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Career==\nAfter completing school, Kohli found an agent and began working in television, making appearances in established series ''[[Holby City]]'' (2012) and ''[[EastEnders]]'' (2013), as well as advertisements for major brands, such as [[Sony]] and [[Heineken]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} Although no longer his focus, he continued to work on the stage as well, including a period of time at the [[Royal National Theatre]] working with acclaimed director [[Howard Davies (director)|Howard Davies]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\nShortly after moving to [[Los Angeles]],{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} Kohli was cast in a lead role in the television series, ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]'' (2015\u201319), as Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti.<ref name = Rolling>{{cite web|author=Rachel Weber |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/actor-rahul-kohli-on-converting-izombie-costars-to-gaming-2-191669/ |title=Actor Rahul Kohli on Converting \u2018iZombie\u2019 Costars to Gaming |publisher=Rolling Stone|date=9 March 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> He appeared in all 71 episodes of the show. Other notable credits include the 2018 film, ''[[Happy Anniversary (2018 film)|Happy Anniversary]]'';<ref>{{cite web|author=Amanda N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/rahul-kohli-happy-anniversary-netflix-denis-menochet-lior-ashkenazi-entebbe-movie-1201903469/ |title=Rahul Kohli Joins Netflix Comedy \u2018Happy Anniversary\u2019; Denis M\u00e9nochet & Lior Ashkenazi Cast In \u2018Entebbe\u2019 |publisher=Deadline |date=7 February 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'' (2017\u201319);<ref>{{cite web|author=Christina Radish |url=https://collider.com/rahul-kohli-supergirl-season-2-interview/ |title=\u2018Supergirl\u2019: Rahul Kohli on His Character\u2019s Arrival in National City on Tonight\u2019s Episode|publisher=Collider |date=24 April 2017 |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Sam Stone |url=https://www.cbr.com/supergirl-rahul-kohli-season-5/ |title=Supergirl Welcomes Back iZombie's Rahul Kohli for Season 5 |publisher=CRB.com|date=28 August 2019|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> and the animated TV series, ''[[Harley Quinn (TV series)|Harley Quinn]]'' (2019\u20132020). Kohli will also be appearing in the upcoming series, ''[[The Haunting of Bly Manor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Anthony D'Alessandro |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/netflix-haunting-of-bly-manor-cast-izombie-rahul-kohli-catherine-parker-1202708101/ |title=\u2018iZombie\u2019s Rahul Kohli Joins \u2018Haunting Of Bly Manor\u2019 Posse; Catherine Parker Returning To Netflix Anthology Series |publisher=Deadline |date=30 August 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>     \n\n==Personal life==\nKohli is a fan of [[Liverpool football club|Liverpool Football Club]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}} He is very active on [[Twitter]] and an avid gamer.<ref name = Rolling>{{cite web|author=Rachel Weber |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/actor-rahul-kohli-on-converting-izombie-costars-to-gaming-2-191669/ |title=Actor Rahul Kohli on Converting \u2018iZombie\u2019 Costars to Gaming |publisher=Rolling Stone|date=9 March 2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> Since 2015, he has featured in several [[Rooster Teeth]] videos for [[Rooster Teeth#Funhaus|Funhaus]], [[Kinda Funny]], and [[Achievement Hunter]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Partial filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''The Vacancy''\n| Tom\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Alone Together''\n| Ahmed\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''I'll Be Home Soon''\n| Waseem\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Gangsters Gamblers Geezers''\n| Dev\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Happy Anniversary (2018 film)|Happy Anniversary]]''\n| Ed\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''My Holiday Hostage Hell''\n| Navi\n| Episode: \"West Papau\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Holby City]]''\n| Cal Nelson\n| Episode: \"Blood Money\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[EastEnders]]''\n| Manager\n| Episode: 16 April 2013\n|-\n| 2015\u20132019\n| ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]''\n| Dr. Ravi Chakrabarti\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2017\u201319\n| ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]''\n| Jack Spheer\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\u20132020\n| ''[[Harley Quinn (TV series)|Harley Quinn]]''\n| [[Scarecrow (DC Comics)|Dr. Jonathan Crane / Scarecrow]]<br>(voice)\n| Recurring role\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The Rocketeer (2019 TV series)|The Rocketeer]]''\n| Aarush Cheena (voice)\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The Haunting of Bly Manor]]''\n|\n|\n|}\n\n===Web series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Red vs. Blue]]''\n| Male Tex\n| Episode: \"Get Bent\"